WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.298
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.330 --> 00:05.628
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:08.370 --> 00:09.803
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:09.840 --> 00:11.808
THE AFGHAN PEOPLE
NEVER WANTED THIS COMMUNISM.

00:11.840 --> 00:13.501
THE REST OF THE WORLD
MUST KNOW THIS.

00:13.540 --> 00:15.872
I RISK MY LIFE
TO COME HERE.

00:15.910 --> 00:18.799
SOMETHING DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT
TO ME ABOUT ZINAIDA.

00:18.850 --> 00:20.977
SHE'S GONNA MEET SENATORS,
CABINET MEMBERS.

00:21.020 --> 00:22.715
SHE COULD MEET
THE PRESIDENT.

00:22.750 --> 00:26.311
IF, BY SOME WILD CHANCE,
THERE IS SOMETHING HERE,

00:26.360 --> 00:27.987
WE NEED TO KNOW.

00:28.020 --> 00:30.159
Philip: I WAS GOING OVER
THE FILES AGAIN OF MARTHA'S.

00:30.190 --> 00:32.226
NINE PEOPLE ARE GETTING
SECURITY CLEARANCES

00:32.260 --> 00:33.659
FOR A NEW
NORTHROP FACTORY.

00:33.700 --> 00:36.191
THE CENTRE WILL WANT LISA
IN THERE SOON.

00:36.230 --> 00:38.494
LIFE GETS PRETTY BORING
WHEN YOU STOP DRINKING.

00:38.530 --> 00:40.498
SO, TELL ME ABOUT YOU.
WHAT KIND OF WORK DO YOU DO?

00:40.540 --> 00:43.703
ASSEMBLY LINE.
IT'S A COMPANY CALLED NORTHROP.

00:43.740 --> 00:45.503
I'VE BEEN THINKING,

00:45.540 --> 00:48.429
AND WHAT I REALLY WANT THIS YEAR
IS TO GET BAPTIZED.

00:50.780 --> 00:53.715
THESE ARE GREAT.
YOU GUYS LOOK 25.

00:55.280 --> 00:58.010
WE'VE NEVER USED
SOMEONE THIS YOUNG BEFORE.

00:58.050 --> 01:00.109
THE CIA'S A HARD TARGET.

01:02.630 --> 01:07.750
* THE ITSY-BITSY SPIDER
WENT UP THE WATERSPOUT *

01:07.800 --> 01:11.520
* DOWN CAME THE RAIN
AND WASHED THE SPIDER OUT *

01:11.570 --> 01:13.765
[ GASPSS ]
OH, MY GOD, CLARK.

01:13.800 --> 01:15.028
LOOK AT HER.

01:15.070 --> 01:16.606
* DRIED UP ALL THE RAIN

01:16.640 --> 01:17.868
WHAT'S HER NAM E?

01:17.910 --> 01:19.104
THAT'S ALICIA.

01:19.140 --> 01:20.869
ISN'T SHE SOMETHING?
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:20.910 --> 01:23.378
OH, COULDN'T YOU JUST
EAT HER UP?
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:23.410 --> 01:25.605
COULD WE HAVE A MINUTE?
OF COURSE.

01:25.650 --> 01:28.073
THANK YOU.

01:31.920 --> 01:33.217
YOU GOT TO ADMIT.

01:33.260 --> 01:35.558
I -- WE'RE NOT
BUYING ONE TODAY.

01:35.590 --> 01:36.887
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:36.930 --> 01:38.750
JOKE ALL YOU LIKE, CLARK,
BUT THIS IS SERIOUS.

01:38.790 --> 01:40.553
I-I KNOW.

01:40.600 --> 01:41.919
AND THIS ISN'T
JUST FOR ME.

01:41.960 --> 01:44.064
THINK ABOUT WHAT IT WOULD
BE LIKE TO COME HOME

01:44.100 --> 01:46.068
AND HAVE THAT LITTLE GIRL
RUNNING TOWARDS YOU

01:46.100 --> 01:48.568
AND THROWING HER ARMS
AROUND YOU.

01:48.600 --> 01:52.138
WE HAVE A LOT
OF LOVE NOW, BUT...

01:52.180 --> 01:53.772
THERE ARE OTHER KINDS
OF LOVE.

01:58.650 --> 02:00.072
Child:
YOU CAN'T CATCH ME!

02:00.120 --> 02:02.486
I'M COMING!

02:02.520 --> 02:04.647
WAIT FOR ME!
LET'S PLAY PRINCESSES!

02:04.690 --> 02:06.089
GO GET 'EM.

02:06.120 --> 02:08.759
[ CHILDREN SHOUTING PLAYFULLY,
LAUGHTER ]

02:08.790 --> 02:10.587
CUTE.
[ Laughing ] OH, I KNOW.

02:10.630 --> 02:11.949
YEAH.

02:11.990 --> 02:15.653
MY KIDS HAVEN'T PLAYED
LIKE THIS IN A LONG TIME.

02:18.870 --> 02:22.658
YOU WEREN'T AT
THE MEETING AGAIN.

02:22.710 --> 02:24.598
I'LL GET THERE.

02:24.640 --> 02:26.972
YOU'RE WHITE-KNUCKLING IT.
YOU KNOW THAT DOESN'T WORK.

02:27.010 --> 02:29.274
YOU NEED THE MEETINGS
AND THE SUPPORT RIGHT NOW.

02:29.310 --> 02:30.504
[ SIGHS ]

02:30.550 --> 02:31.778
WHEN SOMEONE FALLS
LIKE MAURICE,

02:31.810 --> 02:33.118
HANGING ON
DOESN'T ALWAYS HELP,

02:33.150 --> 02:34.447
BECAUSE THEN YOU'RE
GONNA FALL, TOO.

02:34.480 --> 02:36.789
YEAH, SO I SHOULD
JUST LET HIM GO?

02:36.820 --> 02:39.311
I THINK YOU
NEED A BREAK.

02:42.020 --> 02:45.148
LISTEN, MY MOM
HAS THIS PLACE.

02:45.190 --> 02:46.828
SHE JUST MOVED
INTO A NURSING HOME.

02:46.860 --> 02:48.953
OH, I'M SORRY.
IT'S OKAY.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.524
THE HOUSE IS
COMPLETELY EMPTY.

02:50.570 --> 02:51.821
WHY DON'T YOU GO
STAY THERE FOR A WHILE,

02:51.870 --> 02:53.292
GET YOURSELF TOGETHER?

02:53.340 --> 02:54.534
[ SCOFFS ]
I CAN'T DO THAT.

02:54.570 --> 02:55.798
WHY NOT?

02:55.840 --> 02:57.205
IT'S 50 MILES FROM HERE.

02:57.240 --> 02:59.162
IT'S A GREAT NEIGHBORHOOD,
GREAT SCHOOLS.

02:59.210 --> 03:01.007
IT'LL GIVE YOU A CHANCE
TO GET BACK ON YOUR FEET,

03:01.040 --> 03:02.302
BE WITH THE KIDS.

03:02.350 --> 03:04.477
COME ON. HOW LONG
ARE THEY GONNA SLEEP

03:04.510 --> 03:06.171
ON YOUR SISTER'S FLOOR?

03:06.220 --> 03:09.712
SEE HOW YOU DO WITHOUT MAURICE,
EVEN FOR A FEW WEEKS.

03:09.750 --> 03:14.050
IT'LL ALSO GIVE HIM
A CHANCE TO TURN THINGS AROUND.

03:14.090 --> 03:16.684
YOU COULD STILL COME BACK HERE,
DRIVE TO WORK.

03:18.590 --> 03:21.889
YOU CAN'T LIVE LIKE THIS,
LISA.

03:21.930 --> 03:25.491
LET ME HELP YOU OUT.

03:25.530 --> 03:27.191
I'D LIKE TO.

03:38.750 --> 03:41.275
[ COUGHS ]

03:44.120 --> 03:45.712
[ SNIFFLES ]

03:52.090 --> 03:55.526
YOU ASKED WHAT I CAN DO
TO HELP HER.

03:55.560 --> 03:57.528
WELL, I HAVE AN IDEA.

04:02.070 --> 04:04.368
ZINAIDA PREOBRAZHENSKAYA?

04:04.410 --> 04:08.073
I THINK SHE JUST MIGHT BE
A RUSSIAN SPY.

04:08.110 --> 04:11.273
[ SIGHS ]

04:11.310 --> 04:12.868
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR MIND.

04:12.920 --> 04:15.718
IF I CAN PROVE IT,
WE'LL ARREST HER.

04:15.750 --> 04:18.617
THEN THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
MY GOVERNMENT CAN MAKE A TRADE.

04:20.290 --> 04:22.087
FOR NINA.

04:22.120 --> 04:25.556
THE FBI WILL
GO TO BAT FOR HER.

04:25.590 --> 04:27.228
SHE WAS OUR ASSET.

04:27.260 --> 04:29.592
THEY WON'T LEAVE HER TO ROT IN
THE GULAG IF THEY HAVE A CHOICE.

04:31.100 --> 04:33.239
PRISONER EXCHANGE.
[ SIGHS ]

04:33.270 --> 04:35.238
YOU GOT SOMETHING BE'I'I'ER?

04:35.270 --> 04:36.931
[ SIGHS ]

04:36.970 --> 04:39.438
I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

04:39.480 --> 04:42.574
"MAYBE HE'S TRYING TO TRAP ME
THE WAY I TRAPPED HIM."

04:42.610 --> 04:46.569
THAT MAKES SENSE.
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT, OLEG?

04:46.620 --> 04:52.149
I DON'T CARE ENOUGH ABOUT YOU
TO GO TO ALL THAT TROUBLE.

04:52.190 --> 04:54.784
SO, WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT ZINAIDA?

04:56.630 --> 04:58.484
NOTHING.

04:59.830 --> 05:01.092
OKAY.

05:01.130 --> 05:03.769
[ SIGHS ]
I'M BEING HONEST.

05:03.800 --> 05:07.167
IF ZINAIDA
IS ONE OF OURS...

05:07.200 --> 05:10.761
[SNIFFS] I DON'T KNOW.

05:10.810 --> 05:13.608
WELL, THIS IS WHAT I GOT.

05:13.640 --> 05:16.973
YOU SAY YOU WANT
TO HELP HER?

05:17.010 --> 05:18.477
FIND OUT.

05:59.420 --> 06:02.480
[ METAL THUDDING ]

06:02.530 --> 06:06.057
WHEN YOU LAND, TAKE A WEEK,
BE IN TOUCH WITH US NEXT FRIDAY.

06:06.090 --> 06:08.149
LISTEN, YOU GOT WHAT
YOU NEEDED FROM ME.

06:08.200 --> 06:10.998
LEAVE ME ALONE NOW.

06:11.030 --> 06:13.897
I CAN'T DO THAT.

06:13.940 --> 06:15.498
I DON'T BELONG TO YOU.

06:15.540 --> 06:17.337
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

06:17.370 --> 06:19.361
I HELPED YOU.
I GOT YOU TO THE AFGHAN GROUP.

06:19.410 --> 06:21.503
YOUSAF,
THIS ISN'T ABOUT ME.

06:21.540 --> 06:25.340
THIS IS ABOUT WAR
AND PEACE FOR ALL OF US.

06:25.380 --> 06:28.019
SO, WHEN YOU GET BACK,

06:28.050 --> 06:29.847
START TO MAKE PEACE

06:29.890 --> 06:32.188
WITH THE FUNDIOI'VMIESN-IALIST FACT IONS

06:32.220 --> 06:34.586
[ SCOFFS ] MAKE PEACE?

06:34.620 --> 06:37.350
LOOK AT THE PEOPLE
YOU'RE FIGHTING WITH.

06:37.390 --> 06:39.381
JUST TODAY, DID YOU HEAR?

06:39.430 --> 06:41.398
10 OF YOUR SOLDIERS
FLAYED ALIVE

06:41.430 --> 06:43.125
AND LEFI' IN THE SUN
TO ROT.

06:44.900 --> 06:47.198
YOU'RE FIGHTING
BARBARIANS.

06:47.240 --> 06:52.200
US NOW. YOU NEXT.
AND MAYBE SOONER THAN YOU THINK.

06:52.240 --> 06:53.730
IT'S HAPPENING NOW.

06:53.780 --> 06:56.237
THE FUNDAMENTALISTS
ARE EVERWVHERE IN PAKISTAN.

06:56.280 --> 06:58.874
OUR OFFICERS
ARE GROWING THEIR BEARDS.

06:58.910 --> 07:00.411
WE HAD OUR ASSESSMENTS.

07:00.450 --> 07:02.748
THE COLONEL ADDED
A NEW QUESTION --

07:02.790 --> 07:05.441
"HOW RELIGIOUS ARE YOU,
SCALE OF 1 TO 10?"

07:05.490 --> 07:08.288
I SAID 5 --
ALREADY A LIE.

07:08.320 --> 07:11.721
MOST OF THE OTHER DIVISION HEADS
SAID 10.

07:11.760 --> 07:14.797
NEXT TIME...

07:14.830 --> 07:16.923
SAY 10, YOUSAF.

07:16.970 --> 07:19.393
Announcer: [ British accent ]
THE CONFIRMED DEATH TOLL

07:19.430 --> 07:21.591
NOW STANDS
AT 64 SOVIET SOLDIERS

07:21.640 --> 07:24.404
AND 112 AFGHAN ARMY SOLDIERS.

07:24.440 --> 07:27.136
BUT REPORTS OF FUEL
AND ORDNANCE EXPLOSIONS

07:27.180 --> 07:30.900
IN THE SALANG TUNNEL INDICATE
THE TOLL COULD GO MUCH HIGHER.

07:30.950 --> 07:32.645
YOU'RE LISTENING TO "BBC NEWS."

07:32.680 --> 07:33.942
[ RADIO SHUTS OFF ]

07:36.820 --> 07:39.983
YOU LOOK WORRIED.

07:40.020 --> 07:41.954
[ SIGHS ]

07:41.990 --> 07:46.654
MARTHA TOOK ME TO A FOSTER-CARE
PLACE TO LOOK AT KIDS.

07:48.530 --> 07:49.827
[ SIGHS ]

07:49.870 --> 07:52.122
THEY'RE SO LITTLE.

07:52.170 --> 07:55.765
REMEMBER WHEN WALKING
WITHOUT FALLING ON THEIR FACES

07:55.800 --> 07:57.461
WAS A BIG DEAL?

07:57.510 --> 07:59.137
REMEMBER HENRY?

07:59.170 --> 08:01.604
[ LAUGHS ]

08:01.640 --> 08:03.642
PAIGE WAS SO GRACEFUL.

08:03.680 --> 08:06.342
PAIGE?
NO, SHE WASN'T.

08:06.380 --> 08:07.938
YES, SHE WAS.

08:07.980 --> 08:09.789
PHILIP, DON'T YOU REMEMBER
THAT WHOLE SUMMER

08:09.820 --> 08:11.219
SHE KEPT FALLING DOWN?

08:12.820 --> 08:15.687
OH, YEAH. OH, YEAH.

08:15.720 --> 08:18.826
THE SUMMER
OF SKINNED KNEES.

08:24.500 --> 08:28.334
I COULD ALMOST DO IT
IF IT KEPT MARTHA ON TRACK.

08:33.410 --> 08:35.503
WHERE ARE YOU
WITH KIMBERLY?

08:38.180 --> 08:39.818
I'M SEEING HER
TOMORROW NIGHT,

08:39.850 --> 08:44.480
SO I SHOULD BE
IN THE HOUSE SOON.

08:44.520 --> 08:47.182
WHAT'S SHE LIKE?

08:49.930 --> 08:52.353
YOUNG.

08:59.900 --> 09:02.039
I HAVE TO GO MAKE DINNER.

09:09.080 --> 09:11.344
Henry: BUT JOHN HAS
THE BIGGEST VOCABULARY.

09:11.380 --> 09:13.746
HE'S ALWAYS LIKE, "ALBEIT."
I'M LIKE, "WHAT?"

09:13.780 --> 09:15.668
[ STAN LAUGHS ]

09:15.720 --> 09:18.211
YOU KNOW, I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS -- "ALBEIT."

09:18.250 --> 09:20.514
WHAT GROWN-UP EVEN SAYS
"ALBEIT," RIGHT?

09:20.560 --> 09:23.358
WELL, YOU SHOULD MEET
OUR SPECIAL AGENT IN CHARGE.

09:23.390 --> 09:24.880
IS THAT YOUR BOSS?
YEP.

09:24.930 --> 09:26.181
NO MATTER HOW OLD YOU GET,

09:26.230 --> 09:27.549
YOU'RE STILL WORKING
FOR THE MAN.

09:27.600 --> 09:29.397
[ LAUGHS ]

09:29.430 --> 09:31.022
[ LAUGHS ]

09:31.070 --> 09:33.595
SO, HOW'S MRS. BEEMAN?

09:38.270 --> 09:40.101
FINE. SHE'S GREAT.

09:40.140 --> 09:41.903
MAY I PLEASE CHANGE
THE SUBJECT?

09:41.940 --> 09:43.373
YEAH.
Philip: YEAH.

09:43.410 --> 09:45.878
UM, I'D LIKE TO BUY
A DRESS FOR MY BAPTISM.

09:45.910 --> 09:48.708
OH, HEY, THIS BAPTISM --
I THINK THAT'S GREAT.

09:48.750 --> 09:50.047
CONGRATULATIONS.

09:50.090 --> 09:52.888
THANK YOU.
UM, SO, ABOUT THE DRESS --

09:52.920 --> 09:54.717
I DON'T NEED ANYTHING FANCY.

09:54.760 --> 09:57.422
I'LL USE MY OWN MONEY, BUT
I JUST NEED SOMEONE TO TAKE ME.

09:57.460 --> 09:59.257
DON'T YOU HAVE A DRESS --
I CAN TAKE YOU.

10:02.630 --> 10:06.293
YOU HAVE
THE PACIFIC TOURS SEMINAR, SO...

10:06.330 --> 10:08.298
I CAN TAKE HER
TO BUY A DRESS.

10:20.350 --> 10:23.683
[ TOOLS CLATTERING ]

10:26.320 --> 10:29.289
Woman: TOM! DINNER!

10:31.290 --> 10:32.587
FIVE MORE MINUTES.

10:32.630 --> 10:34.120
[ CLATTERING CONTINUES ]

10:46.640 --> 10:49.108
[ A FLOCK OF SEAGULLS'S
"I RAN" PLAYS ]

10:49.140 --> 10:53.179
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
* I WALKED ALONG THE AVENUE

10:53.220 --> 10:55.142
* I NEVER THOUGHT I'D MEET

10:55.180 --> 10:57.785
GIMME ONE SEC.
* A GIRL LIKE YOU

10:57.820 --> 11:01.517
* MEET A GIRL LIKE YOU

11:02.660 --> 11:04.184
HEY, THERE, COWBOY.

11:04.230 --> 11:07.495
HEY.

11:07.530 --> 11:10.294
COULDN'T WE GO SOMEWHERE
A LITTLE MORE PRIVATE?

11:10.330 --> 11:13.367
OH, YEAH. NO, IT'S JUST, UH,
MY FRIENDS ALWAYS COME HERE,

11:13.400 --> 11:15.038
SO I FIGURED
I'D GET A RIDE WITH THEM,

11:15.070 --> 11:16.469
AND THAT WAY
I COULD SEE YOU.

11:16.500 --> 11:17.808
YEAH, YEAH, NO.

11:17.840 --> 11:19.205
I JUST THOUGHT IT'D BE
US HANGING OUT,

11:19.240 --> 11:20.537
NOT A WHOLE GROUP.

11:20.580 --> 11:22.844
NO, NO, I WAS
THINKING THAT, TOO,

11:22.880 --> 11:25.303
BUT WE'LL JUST TOKE UP HERE,
AND THEN WE CAN LEAVE,

11:25.350 --> 11:27.318
AND...I DON'T KNOW.
HEY.

11:27.350 --> 11:28.874
KIMMY.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.715
WHO'S THIS?

11:32.760 --> 11:36.389
UH...
HE'S A FRIEND OF MINE.

11:36.420 --> 11:37.523
WHAT KIND
OF FRIEND?

11:37.560 --> 11:38.822
IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

11:38.860 --> 11:41.499
SHE ASKED ME TO COME
GIVE HER A RIDE.

11:41.530 --> 11:42.997
I COULD GIVE YOU A RIDE,
KIMMY.

11:43.030 --> 11:45.669
GREAT.
YOU SHOULD GIVE HER A RIDE.

11:45.700 --> 11:46.894
TAKE CARE, KIMMY.

11:46.940 --> 11:49.033
WAIT, JAM ES.
KIM MY.

11:49.070 --> 11:51.004
JAMES, THEY'RE IDIOTS.
PLEASE.

11:51.040 --> 11:54.373
YEAH, IN
WHEATLY HIGH SCHOOL JACKETS.

11:54.410 --> 11:56.071
GEORGETOWN?

11:56.110 --> 11:57.998
WELL, I WENT TO
SUMMER SCHOOL THERE.

11:58.050 --> 11:59.677
ARE YOU EVEN OLD ENOUGH
TO DRIVE YET?

11:59.710 --> 12:02.019
I WILL BE.
WHEN?

12:02.050 --> 12:05.019
LIKE EIGHT --
NO, SEVEN MONTHS.

12:05.050 --> 12:07.052
* AURORA COMES IN VIEW

12:07.090 --> 12:08.853
GREAT. COME ON,
I'LL TAKE YOU HOME.

12:08.890 --> 12:11.427
* AND I RAN,
I RAN SO FAR AWAY *
UH, WAIT.

12:11.460 --> 12:14.054
N-NO, D-- DON'T
TAKE ME HOME YET.

12:14.100 --> 12:16.898
* I JUST RAN
[ SIGHS ]

12:16.930 --> 12:19.023
* I RAN ALL NIGHT AND DAY

12:19.070 --> 12:20.765
WHERE DO YOUR FOLKS
THINK YOU ARE RIGHT NOW?

12:20.800 --> 12:22.097
* I COULDN'T GET AWAY
A MOVIE.

12:22.140 --> 12:24.199
I CAN SAY WHATEVER.
THEY DON'T CARE.

12:24.240 --> 12:26.299
I SHOULD GET YOU BACK.

12:28.940 --> 12:30.703
WHAT'S THE RUSH?
COME ON.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.103
I'M GONNA BE DRIVING
ALL NIGHT AS IT IS.

12:32.150 --> 12:33.913
WELL, WHEN ARE YOU
GONNA BE BACK?

12:33.950 --> 12:35.542
[ SIGHS ]
LISTEN, KIMMY.

12:35.580 --> 12:36.888
THIS WHOLE AGE THING...

12:36.920 --> 12:38.717
BUT Y-YOU'RE NOT OLD.

12:38.750 --> 12:40.058
YOU'RE YOUNG.

12:40.090 --> 12:42.558
AGE IS JUST A NUMBER.

12:42.590 --> 12:45.229
[ SIGHS ]

12:45.260 --> 12:47.626
YOU LIKE HANGING OUT
WITH ME, RIGHT?

12:47.660 --> 12:51.266
YES, I --
I REALLY LIKE YOU.

12:51.300 --> 12:53.063
BUT I LIVE IN NEW YORK,

12:53.100 --> 12:55.466
AND WHEN I'M DOWN HERE,
I'M BUSY WITH WORK.

12:55.500 --> 12:57.229
* REACHED OUT A HAND
TO TOUCH YOUR FACE *
COME ON.

12:57.270 --> 12:58.567
YOU SAW WHAT
JUST HAPPENED.

12:58.610 --> 13:00.635
WHEN PEOPLE SEE US TOGETHER,
IT'S WEIRD.

13:00.680 --> 13:03.103
* ...FROM MY VIEW

13:03.150 --> 13:04.572
* APPEARING FROM MY VIEW

13:04.610 --> 13:07.909
WELL, THEN, LET'S JUST
HANG OUT IN PRIVATE.

13:07.950 --> 13:11.613
* REACHED OUT A HAND
TO TRY AGAIN *
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
ON THE 11th?

13:11.650 --> 13:14.255
* I'M FLOATING IN
A BEAM OF LIGHT WITH YOU *
THE 11th?

13:14.290 --> 13:16.451
MY PARENTS ARE GONNA BE
AT A BIG FUNDRAISER.

13:16.490 --> 13:17.752
* A BEAM OF LIGHT WITH YOU

13:17.790 --> 13:20.293
YOU SHOULD COME BY.

13:20.330 --> 13:22.628
* AND I RAN
SMOKE SOME POT.

13:22.660 --> 13:25.458
* I RAN SO FAR AWAY

13:25.500 --> 13:27.593
PLEASE.

13:27.640 --> 13:31.098
* I JUST RAN,
I RAN ALL NIGHT AND DAY *

13:31.140 --> 13:32.835
[ SIGHS ]

13:39.680 --> 13:41.011
Elizabeth:
IT'S A SUCCULENT.

13:41.050 --> 13:42.449
IT GROWS LIKE A WEED
AND REQUIRES MINIMAL EFFORT.

13:42.480 --> 13:43.947
MY KIND OF PLANT.
THANK YOU.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.446
[ LAUGHS ]

13:45.490 --> 13:46.980
MOTHER-IN-LAW'S TONGUE --
THAT'S WHAT IT'S CALLED.

13:47.020 --> 13:48.317
[ LAUGHS ]

13:50.330 --> 13:52.958
IT'S SO STRANGE BEING
HERE IN YOUR HOUSE --

13:53.000 --> 13:54.319
Y-YOUR MOM'S HOUSE.

13:54.360 --> 13:56.863
THIS IS, UH...

13:56.900 --> 13:58.322
IT'S WHAT?

14:00.040 --> 14:01.291
[ SIGHS ]

14:01.340 --> 14:02.796
I DON'T KNOW.

14:02.840 --> 14:07.038
I WAS ALWAYS AFRAID
THAT IF I LEFT MAURICE,

14:07.080 --> 14:10.470
I'D BE LOST, LONELY.

14:10.510 --> 14:12.307
YOU'RE NOT.

14:12.350 --> 14:14.477
NO, I'M NOT.

14:14.520 --> 14:15.817
MM.

14:15.850 --> 14:18.978
I DON'T MISS HIM.

14:19.020 --> 14:21.215
AND I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
HIS TEMPER OR HIS MOODS.

14:21.260 --> 14:22.511
I DON'T MISS HIM.

14:22.560 --> 14:24.482
MM.
HIS PRESENCE.

14:24.530 --> 14:25.679
MM.

14:25.730 --> 14:27.322
[ SIGHS ]

14:27.360 --> 14:29.658
THE KIDS ARE HAVING
A HARDER TIME.

14:29.700 --> 14:30.826
AW.

14:30.870 --> 14:32.326
TEDDY STARTED
WETTING THE BED.

14:32.370 --> 14:33.735
OOH.

14:33.770 --> 14:34.998
I KNOW.
IT'S BREAKING MY HEART.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.837
BUT MAURICE HAS BEEN
GREAT ABOUT IT.

14:36.870 --> 14:38.337
STAYING IN THEIR LIVES.
YEAH.

14:38.370 --> 14:40.031
HE TALKS TO THE KIDS
EVERY NIGHT.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.537
I HEAR THEM ON THE PHONE --
TWO HOURS, AT LEAST.

14:42.580 --> 14:45.401
ONE FOOT IN FRONT
OF THE OTHER, YOU KNOW?

14:45.450 --> 14:46.872
YEAH.

14:48.880 --> 14:51.019
COACH BAG? NICE.

14:51.050 --> 14:53.518
I KNOW.
DO YOU LIKE IT?

14:53.560 --> 14:55.187
FANCY.

14:55.220 --> 14:57.188
[ LAUGHS ]

14:57.230 --> 14:59.084
GUESS WHAT.

14:59.130 --> 15:01.690
NORTHROP HAS A PLANT
10 MILES FROM HERE.

15:01.730 --> 15:02.890
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

15:02.930 --> 15:05.023
NO.
I PUT IN FOR A TRANSFER.

15:05.070 --> 15:07.698
OH, I WOULD LOVE TO PUT
THAT 50-MILE COMMUTE TO BED.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.037
YEAH.

15:09.070 --> 15:10.560
AND SINCE I HAVE
SECURITY CLEARANCE,

15:10.610 --> 15:12.760
IF SOMETHING COMES UP, MY NAME
GOES TO THE TOP OF THE LIST.

15:12.810 --> 15:15.370
FINGERS CROSSED.
THAT'D BE GREAT.

15:15.410 --> 15:17.048
I'M ON A ROLL.

15:17.080 --> 15:20.379
PLUS, I GOT
MY LUCKY CHARM -- YOU.

15:20.420 --> 15:23.446
[ LAUGHS ]

15:23.490 --> 15:25.742
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:57.120 --> 15:59.588
[ SIGHS ] CHEERS.

15:59.620 --> 16:02.453
BUDEM.

16:02.490 --> 16:04.788
[ LAUGHS ]

16:06.160 --> 16:08.025
[ SIGHS ]

16:11.200 --> 16:12.622
HMM?

16:58.680 --> 16:59.908
HMM.

17:11.190 --> 17:13.590
DA.

18:17.760 --> 18:19.728
BUDEM.

18:19.760 --> 18:22.126
DA, BUDEM.

18:26.330 --> 18:28.469
THIS?

18:28.500 --> 18:31.799
YOUR TASTE
IS RIDICULOUS, DAD.

18:31.840 --> 18:34.229
IS IT?
YOU THINK SO?

18:34.280 --> 18:36.407
[ LAUGHS ]

18:36.440 --> 18:40.149
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

18:40.180 --> 18:41.909
OKAY.

18:41.950 --> 18:43.941
HOW ABOUT...

18:47.620 --> 18:49.781
OKAY, FASHION QUEEN,
YOU PICK ONE.

18:49.820 --> 18:52.129
OKAY.

18:55.800 --> 18:57.665
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

19:01.200 --> 19:03.259
[ SIGHS ]

19:03.310 --> 19:05.107
I'VE GOT IT.

19:05.140 --> 19:07.700
I HAVE GOT IT.

19:13.680 --> 19:16.319
YEAH. TRY IT ON.

19:16.350 --> 19:17.942
DAD, THIS IS WAY TOO --

19:17.990 --> 19:20.959
JUST TRY IT ON.
I'LL BUY YOU THE DRESS.

19:20.990 --> 19:23.015
ARE YOU SURE?
YES, I'M SURE.

19:23.060 --> 19:25.984
REALLY?
OF COURSE.

19:26.030 --> 19:27.292
THAN KS, DAD.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.218
YOU'RE WELCOME.

19:32.370 --> 19:35.339
[ SIGHS ]

19:35.370 --> 19:38.203
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

19:38.240 --> 19:41.038
HEY, REMEMBER THAT WOMAN
AT THE EST THING? TORI?

19:41.080 --> 19:43.548
OH, THE ONE WHO HAD ALL
THOSE HORRIBLE PROBLEMS

19:43.580 --> 19:44.842
WITH HER FATHER?

19:44.880 --> 19:46.177
YEAH.

19:46.210 --> 19:48.872
SHE CALLED THE FBI...

19:48.920 --> 19:50.319
AND ASKED FOR ME.

19:50.350 --> 19:53.558
AS IN CALLED CALLED?

19:53.590 --> 19:55.808
ASKED ME OUT.

19:55.860 --> 19:58.226
[ CHUCKLES ]
I GUESS WOMEN DO THAT NOW.

19:58.260 --> 19:59.659
EST WOMEN DO THAT.

19:59.690 --> 20:00.998
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:01.030 --> 20:02.497
THEY'RE BEING THEMSELVES.

20:02.530 --> 20:04.327
I THOUGHT THE WHOLE POINT
OF GOING TO EST

20:04.370 --> 20:07.168
WAS TO GET SANDRA BACK.

20:07.200 --> 20:09.498
YEAH.

20:09.540 --> 20:11.508
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
THAT'S HAPPENING.

20:11.540 --> 20:13.007
AH.

20:13.040 --> 20:14.905
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW LONG IT'S BEEN

20:14.940 --> 20:16.498
SINCE I'VE BEEN
ON A DATE?

20:16.540 --> 20:18.679
I DON'T -- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE WOULD TALK ABOUT.

20:18.710 --> 20:21.042
I-I COULDN'T TALK TO SANDRA,
AND I LIVED WITH HER.

20:22.620 --> 20:24.918
HOW'S MATTHEW DEALING
WITH ALL THIS?

20:24.950 --> 20:27.384
HE PRETTY MUCH HATES ME.

20:30.930 --> 20:33.057
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOU SHOULD DO?

20:33.090 --> 20:34.694
WHAT?

20:34.730 --> 20:37.369
SPEND TIME ALONE WITH HIM
NOW THAT YOU HAVE THE CHANCE.

20:37.400 --> 20:40.198
'CAUSE YOU GET HIM AWAY
FROM THE OTHER PARENT,

20:40.230 --> 20:41.731
AND [SIGHS]

20:41.770 --> 20:44.409
THEY'RE JUST A WHOLE
DIFFERENT PERSON ONE-ON-ONE.

20:44.440 --> 20:45.737
YEAH?

20:45.770 --> 20:49.877
YEAH. AND WITHOUT --
WITHOUT THAT OTHER [SIGHS]

20:49.910 --> 20:52.572
WHATEVER YOU WANT TO
CALL IT -- INFLUENCE.

20:53.920 --> 20:57.742
YOU WANT TO KNOW
THE TRUTH?

20:57.790 --> 20:59.883
I DON'T GET MATTHEW.

20:59.920 --> 21:05.085
H-HE'S --
HE'S A COMPLETE MYSTERY TO ME.

21:05.130 --> 21:09.794
ALL THE PEOPLE
I'VE INVESTIGATED, ARRESTED,

21:09.830 --> 21:14.233
BUT, MAN, THERE'S NOTHING
LIKE A TEENAGE BOY.

21:14.270 --> 21:16.568
RIGHT,
BUT WHEN HE WAS A KID...

21:16.600 --> 21:18.261
OH, IT WAS BETTER, SURE.

21:18.310 --> 21:20.266
WE DID STUFF TOGETHER.

21:20.310 --> 21:23.279
YOU KNOW,
GO TO A CARDINALS GAME.

21:23.310 --> 21:24.572
WATCH TV.

21:24.610 --> 21:25.838
YEAH.

21:28.480 --> 21:31.278
YOU KNOW, I WENT AWAY
UNDERCOVER FOR THREE YEARS.

21:33.120 --> 21:35.315
WOW.

21:35.360 --> 21:37.419
AND WHEN I CAME BACK, I THOUGHT,
YOU KNOW,

21:37.460 --> 21:39.451
HE WAS GONNA BE SO HAPPY
TO SEE ME, LIKE --

21:39.490 --> 21:42.288
LIKE I PICTURED HIM
ALL THE TIME

21:42.330 --> 21:44.298
WHEN I WAS AWAY.

21:50.140 --> 21:53.200
YOU SHOULD BRING
YOUR EST LADY HERE FOR DINNER.

21:55.840 --> 21:57.979
YEAH?
YEAH.

21:58.010 --> 22:00.547
TAKE THE PRESSURE OFF.

22:02.180 --> 22:04.819
YEAH, THAT'D BE NICE.
THANKS.

22:07.360 --> 22:09.681
[ TOOLS CLANGING,
INDISTINCT TALKING ON RADIO ]

22:26.910 --> 22:29.174
[ GROANING ]

23:02.040 --> 23:03.507
[ SCRUBBING ]

23:03.550 --> 23:06.701
7:30.
THEY'RE GOING TO A PLAY.

23:06.750 --> 23:08.342
GOOD.

23:08.380 --> 23:11.349
YOU'LL GET IN THERE AND SEE
WHAT YOU HAVE TO WORK WITH.

23:11.390 --> 23:12.880
[ SPRAY BOTTLE HISSING ]

23:12.920 --> 23:16.913
WHAT I HAVE TO WORK WITH IS
A HORMONAL 15-YEAR-OLD GIRL.

23:16.960 --> 23:19.554
I SAW THE BAPTISM DRESS.

23:19.590 --> 23:23.026
DID YOU LIKE IT?

23:23.060 --> 23:26.359
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
PHILIP?

23:26.400 --> 23:29.699
I TOOK MY DAUGHTER
TO BUY A DRESS.

23:29.740 --> 23:33.528
YOU SEEM TO SUDDENLY THINK
THIS BAPTISM IS A GOOD IDEA.

23:33.580 --> 23:36.936
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO'S BEEN
SINGING WITH THE CHOIR.

23:36.980 --> 23:39.699
YOUR GIRL, KIMBERLY --

23:39.750 --> 23:42.412
SHE HAS NO IDEA HER FATHER'S
IN THE CIA, DOES SHE?

23:42.450 --> 23:44.213
LOOK HOW SHE WOUND UP.

23:44.250 --> 23:46.218
DON'T SAY IT'S THE SAME.

23:46.250 --> 23:48.582
AND DON'T CALL HER
"MY GIRL."

23:50.760 --> 23:54.252
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

24:02.800 --> 24:05.735
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
FOR YOU.

24:05.770 --> 24:07.909
THAT'S DISAPPOINTING.

24:07.940 --> 24:10.647
LOOK, IF THERE WAS
SOMETHING TO KNOW,

24:10.680 --> 24:12.898
I WOULD HAVE
FOUND IT OUT.

24:12.950 --> 24:14.747
I CAN'T GET ANYTHING.

24:14.780 --> 24:17.487
I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING
TO GET.

24:17.520 --> 24:19.784
YEAH?

24:19.820 --> 24:21.412
WHAT'S MORE LIKELY --

24:21.460 --> 24:25.089
ZINAIDA BEING A DOUBLE AGENT
OR YOU TRYING TO SET ME UP?

24:25.130 --> 24:27.792
YOU'RE STILL IN LOVE
WITH HER.

24:30.800 --> 24:33.268
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

24:33.300 --> 24:36.269
WAIT.

24:36.300 --> 24:39.303
YOU LOVE HER.
I WANT TO SAVE HER.

24:39.340 --> 24:41.979
YOU LOVE HER, TOO!

24:44.680 --> 24:47.046
I WANT TO MAKE IT RIGHT.

24:49.350 --> 24:52.842
THIS DEFECTOR
IS OUR ONLY LEVER.

24:52.890 --> 24:57.452
BELIEVE ME
OR DON'T BELIEVE ME,

24:57.490 --> 25:00.186
BUT HOW MUCH TIME
DOES NINA HAVE?

25:06.830 --> 25:08.798
SO, WHAT IS THIS?

25:08.840 --> 25:10.467
BLUE CHEESE.

25:10.500 --> 25:12.536
NOT A FAN
OF THE STINKY CHEESES.

25:12.570 --> 25:14.834
IT'S THE MOST EXPENSIVE
CHEESE I COULD FIND.

25:14.880 --> 25:16.802
KIND OF
AN ACQUIRED TASTE.

25:16.840 --> 25:19.308
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

25:19.350 --> 25:23.684
I WANTED TO CELEBRATE MY GOOD
LUCK WITH MY GOOD FRIEND.

25:23.720 --> 25:25.347
I GOT A CALL
FROM NORTHROP.

25:25.390 --> 25:27.483
THERE'S AN OPENING
IN FUSELAGE ASSEMBLY --

25:27.520 --> 25:30.318
SAME THING I DO NOW,
EXCEPT IN THIS TIME ZONE.

25:30.360 --> 25:31.657
SO, YOU GOT IT?

25:31.690 --> 25:34.557
I GOT IT. [ LAUGHS ]

25:34.600 --> 25:37.194
15-MINUTE COMMUTE,
DOOR-TO-DOOR!

25:37.230 --> 25:38.891
THAT IS SO GREAT.
[ LAUGHS ]

25:38.930 --> 25:40.522
WHAT DO SAY WE DUMP
THE STINKY CHEESE

25:40.570 --> 25:42.037
AND GO TO MANELLI'S
TO CELEBRATE?

25:43.240 --> 25:45.037
DID YOU WIN THE LOTTERY?

25:45.070 --> 25:46.503
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:46.540 --> 25:49.179
NEW CLOTHES,
NEW BAG, MANELLI'S.

25:49.210 --> 25:52.748
[ LAUGHS ]

25:52.780 --> 25:54.668
WHAT?

25:54.720 --> 25:58.713
THIS IS REALLY
CONE OF SILENCE, THOUGH.

25:58.750 --> 26:00.684
OKAY.

26:00.720 --> 26:01.709
SO, I MET THIS GUY.

26:01.760 --> 26:04.183
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SO?

26:04.230 --> 26:06.221
I DIDN'T WANT TO SAY
SOMETHING UNTIL THERE
WAS SOMETHING TO SAY.

26:06.260 --> 26:07.352
IS THERE
SOMETHING TO SAY?

26:07.390 --> 26:08.527
NO.
[ LAUGHS ]

26:08.560 --> 26:10.425
NOT LIKE THAT.
NOT LIKE THAT.

26:10.460 --> 26:12.018
UM...

26:12.070 --> 26:16.689
SO, HE TAKES ME OUT, AND
JUST -- HE ASKS ME QUESTIONS.

26:16.740 --> 26:17.934
QUESTIONS?

26:17.970 --> 26:19.437
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
JUST STUFF ABOUT WORK,

26:19.470 --> 26:21.199
STUFF WE'RE DOING
AT GENERAL DYNAMICS,

26:21.240 --> 26:23.037
AND HE PAYS ME FOR IT.

26:23.080 --> 26:24.900
HMM.

26:24.950 --> 26:27.714
HE WORKS FOR THIS
CONSULTING FIRM, AND THEY --

26:27.750 --> 26:29.775
I GUESS THEY HELP OUT
ALL THE DEFENSE CONTRACTORS.

26:29.820 --> 26:31.549
THEY HELP THEM
WITH THEIR BIDS,

26:31.590 --> 26:35.048
AND I DON'T KNOW REALLY
WHAT IT IS, BUT HE'S NICE.

26:35.090 --> 26:36.580
IS HE CUTE?

26:36.620 --> 26:37.723
YEAH.

26:37.760 --> 26:39.227
HE'S GONNA WANT MORE.

26:39.260 --> 26:41.125
WHAT, SEX?
GOD, I HOPE SO.

26:41.160 --> 26:42.559
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:42.600 --> 26:44.227
BE CAREFUL, CHELLE.
I'M NOT KIDDING.

26:44.270 --> 26:47.262
MM.
LOOK AT ME.

26:47.300 --> 26:49.564
I'M NOT KIDDING.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.101
YOU BE CAREFUL.

26:51.140 --> 26:52.630
YEAH.

26:53.610 --> 26:55.305
MM-HMM.

26:55.340 --> 26:56.898
NAUGHTY.

26:56.940 --> 26:58.476
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:58.510 --> 26:59.772
OOH.

26:59.810 --> 27:00.970
UH-HUH. UH-HUH.

27:01.020 --> 27:02.248
[ LAUGHS ]

27:02.280 --> 27:04.248
HELLO.

27:04.290 --> 27:05.780
HI.

27:07.790 --> 27:11.954
THE NICARAGUANS ARE VERY HAPPY
ABOUT THE BOLAND AMENDMENT.

27:11.990 --> 27:14.458
THE CENTRE WANTED YOU
TO KNOW.

27:14.500 --> 27:16.252
I'LL TELL ELIZABETH.

27:16.300 --> 27:17.995
I KNOW YOU LOST A COMRADE.

27:18.030 --> 27:19.622
MM-HMM.

27:21.640 --> 27:25.337
SHE FELT CLOSE TO LUCIA.
SHE TOOK IT HARD.

27:25.370 --> 27:28.771
ELIZABETH TAKES
THINGS HARD.

27:28.810 --> 27:31.506
I KNOW THAT.

27:31.550 --> 27:34.815
FOR YOUR FRIEND
KIMBERLY.

27:40.820 --> 27:43.459
[ SNIFFS ] AFGHANI?

27:43.490 --> 27:46.186
APPROPRIATELY ENOUGH.
VERY STRONG.

27:46.230 --> 27:49.620
IT'S ONE OF THE IRONIES
OF THIS WORK

27:49.660 --> 27:52.299
THAT SO MANY LIVES
DEPEND UPON

27:52.330 --> 27:56.494
ONE MAN'S RELATIONSHIP
WITH AN ADOLESCENT GIRL.

27:56.540 --> 27:59.464
[ SIGHS ]

27:59.510 --> 28:02.707
YOU DON'T LIKE THAT.

28:02.740 --> 28:05.800
SHE'S 15 YEARS OLD.
DO YOU?

28:05.850 --> 28:08.819
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN
RELIABLY RUN HER

28:08.850 --> 28:10.818
ANY OTHER WAY --
LONG-TERM.

28:10.850 --> 28:13.011
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME
SEE ABOUT THAT?
OF COURSE.

28:13.050 --> 28:16.315
YOU ARE THE ONE IN THE FIELD,
AND YOU'RE THE BEST.

28:16.360 --> 28:18.021
THERE'S NOBODY BETTER.

28:18.060 --> 28:22.156
BUT PAIGE, KIMBERLY,
MARTHA WITH HER BABY FEVER --

28:22.200 --> 28:24.395
THAT'S A LOT FOR ANYONE.

28:24.430 --> 28:28.366
I CAN IMAGINE IT MIGHT BE
CONFUSING, EVEN FOR YOU.

28:31.770 --> 28:33.328
I'M NOT CONFUSED.

28:33.370 --> 28:36.203
"CONFUSED"
IS THE WRONG WORD.

28:37.950 --> 28:39.702
IT'S DIFFICULT
FOR ALL OF US SOMETIMES

28:39.750 --> 28:43.345
TO KEEP IN MIND
THAT WHEN PEOPLE'S LIVES

28:43.380 --> 28:46.178
INTERSECT
WITH OUR OPERATIONS,

28:46.220 --> 28:49.519
IT'S THE OPERATION
THAT'S CRUCIAL.

28:49.560 --> 28:54.020
AND WHEN THE PERSON
INVOLVED IS SO YOUNG...

28:54.060 --> 28:56.221
YOU HAVE A CONSCIENCE,
PHILIP.

28:56.260 --> 28:59.024
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH THAT.

28:59.070 --> 29:02.892
BUT CONSCIENCE
CAN BE DANGEROUS.

29:07.240 --> 29:10.778
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

29:18.590 --> 29:19.818
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:24.590 --> 29:27.229
YEAH, I'M A LITTLE BIT
COUNTRY.

29:27.260 --> 29:31.390
[ LAUGHS ]
THEY'RE ACTUALLY ALMOST CUTE.

29:31.430 --> 29:33.091
COME IN.

29:40.470 --> 29:43.132
NICE PLACE.

29:43.180 --> 29:45.648
IT'S ALL MY STEPMOM.

29:45.680 --> 29:47.819
SHE'S INTO DECOR,

29:47.850 --> 29:50.478
BUT I NEVER LET HER
INTO MY ROOM.

29:50.520 --> 29:52.147
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:54.860 --> 29:57.158
YOU WANT TO SEE IT?

29:57.190 --> 29:59.283
SURE.

29:59.330 --> 30:02.128
OKAY.

30:02.160 --> 30:04.196
[ FLOORBOARDS CREAKING ]

30:21.880 --> 30:23.768
WELCOME TO MY WORLD.

30:23.820 --> 30:24.946
NICE.

30:24.990 --> 30:28.312
HEY,
LOOK WHAT I BROUGHT.

30:31.530 --> 30:33.350
[ SNIFFS ] WOW.

30:33.390 --> 30:35.119
[ LAUGHS ]
DOESN'T EVEN SMELL LIKE...

30:35.160 --> 30:36.320
PIZZA?

30:36.360 --> 30:38.999
[ LAUGHS ] YEAH.

30:45.010 --> 30:49.379
SO, YOU SPEND ALL YOUR TIME
TRYING TO CONVINCE THEM

30:49.410 --> 30:51.970
TO VOTE THE WAY THAT
THE COMPANIES WANT THEM TO VOTE?

30:52.010 --> 30:54.046
YEAH, PRETTY MUCH.

30:54.080 --> 30:56.514
[ CHUCKLES ] WOW.

30:56.550 --> 30:59.144
YEAH, YOU DEFINITELY
NEED A BETTER LIFE.

30:59.190 --> 31:00.339
THAT'S WHY I'M HANGING OUT
WITH YOU.

31:02.020 --> 31:04.818
OR MAYBE I SHOULD BE
WORKING WITH YOUR DAD
IN THE STATE DEPARTMENT.

31:04.860 --> 31:08.023
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH, THINK AGAIN.

31:08.060 --> 31:10.028
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT DIVISION HE'S IN?

31:11.900 --> 31:13.891
AGRICULTURE.

31:13.940 --> 31:16.864
IT'S SO BORING.

31:16.900 --> 31:19.039
HE MUST KNOW A LOT
ABOUT SOIL.

31:19.070 --> 31:20.332
[ LAUGHS ]

31:20.370 --> 31:23.373
YEAH, NO, REALLY,
HE DOES.

31:23.410 --> 31:27.039
WE USED TO HAVE
THIS GARDEN

31:27.080 --> 31:30.516
WHEN MY MOTHER
WAS STILL ALIVE.

31:30.550 --> 31:32.245
I MEAN, MY --
MY REAL MOM.

31:32.290 --> 31:33.518
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:33.550 --> 31:36.189
RIGHT OUT THERE.

31:36.220 --> 31:39.678
HE SHOWED US
HOW TO PLANT SEEDS,

31:39.730 --> 31:42.699
AND ALL DIFFERENT DEPTHS,

31:42.730 --> 31:47.190
AND MY BROTHER AND SISTER,
WHEN THEY WERE STILL AROUND,

31:47.230 --> 31:52.634
WE WOULD JUST, LIKE, WATER
AND WEED AND ALL THAT STUFF.

31:54.410 --> 31:55.775
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:55.810 --> 31:57.539
CARROTS, SQUASH,

31:57.580 --> 32:00.743
THESE LITTLE, TINY,
LIKE, WATERMELON,

32:00.780 --> 32:05.388
CRAPPY WATERMELONS,
LIKE THE SIZE OF A RUBBER BALL.

32:05.420 --> 32:12.223
AND ME AND MY DAD,
WE HAD THESE TWO RAKES.

32:12.260 --> 32:15.889
THERE WAS A BIG ONE,
AND THERE WAS A LITTLE ONE.

32:15.930 --> 32:18.728
AND HE WOULD GO RAKE
ON ONE SIDE,

32:18.770 --> 32:21.398
AND I WOULD RAKE
ON THE OTHER,

32:21.440 --> 32:23.590
AND WE WOULD JUST, LIKE,
MEET IN THE MIDDLE.

32:25.510 --> 32:28.729
IS IT STILL OUT THERE?
THE GARDEN?

32:28.780 --> 32:30.304
NO.

32:30.340 --> 32:32.444
IT'S A LAWN NOW.

32:32.480 --> 32:34.778
MY STEPMOM -- SHE, UH...

32:34.820 --> 32:36.572
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:36.620 --> 32:40.647
SHE S-SAID IT LOOKED
MESSY, SO...

32:40.690 --> 32:42.783
[ SIGHS ]

32:42.820 --> 32:46.950
SHE DOESN'T COOK
OR ANYTHING, YOU KNOW.

32:46.990 --> 32:49.299
SHE'S ALWAYS, LIKE, OUT.

32:49.330 --> 32:52.993
I MEAN, THEY'RE BOTH GONE,
I MEAN, A LOT.

32:53.030 --> 32:56.466
YOU KNOW, SHE'S ON LIKE
3O DIFFERENT FOUNDATIONS.

32:56.500 --> 33:00.834
SHE'S NEVER HERE, AND MY DAD --
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS.

33:00.870 --> 33:01.939
[ SIGHS ]

33:01.980 --> 33:03.299
YOU KNOW, IF YOU TOLD ME

33:03.340 --> 33:05.604
THAT HE HAD ANOTHER
FAMILY SOMEWHERE,

33:05.650 --> 33:09.177
I WOULD SAY, "OKAY, YEAH, GREAT.
THAT EXPLAINS IT."

33:16.990 --> 33:21.029
HEY, DON'T BOGART
THAT JOINT.

33:21.060 --> 33:23.449
YOU SHOULD BE CAREFUL.
IT'S STRONG.
HMM.

33:23.500 --> 33:25.491
I CAN HANDLE IT.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

33:31.710 --> 33:34.372
I HAVE THE GREATEST IDEA.

33:34.410 --> 33:36.469
[ POPCORN POPPING ]

33:36.510 --> 33:38.307
ROCKY ROAD!

33:38.350 --> 33:39.669
OH.
CAN I?

33:39.710 --> 33:42.372
YEAH, UH, JUST TAKE --
TAKE TWO SPOONS.

33:53.360 --> 33:55.726
MMM.

33:55.760 --> 33:56.988
MMM.

33:57.030 --> 33:58.691
YES, PLEASE.

33:58.730 --> 34:01.563
[ LAUGHS ]

34:01.600 --> 34:06.060
I LOVE ANY KIND OF ICE CREAM
WITH STUFF IN IT, YOU KNOW.

34:06.110 --> 34:08.169
THE CRUNCH.

34:08.210 --> 34:10.508
MM!

34:10.540 --> 34:13.338
LET'S PUT POPCORN IN IT.

34:13.380 --> 34:15.917
OPEN IT.

34:19.220 --> 34:20.244
IT'S HOT.

34:20.290 --> 34:21.382
NO, IT'S NOT.

34:21.420 --> 34:22.614
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:23.920 --> 34:25.387
OH.
OHH! OH! OH!

34:25.430 --> 34:26.579
OH, THAT'S HOT.

34:26.630 --> 34:28.222
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:28.260 --> 34:29.522
OH!

34:29.560 --> 34:32.597
SEE, DUMBO?

34:34.900 --> 34:38.404
YOU KNOW WHAT
THIS MEANS?

34:40.970 --> 34:42.870
WAR'
[ SQUEALS ]

34:42.910 --> 34:44.104
JUST GOT REAL --

34:44.150 --> 34:45.378
[ LAUGHS ]

34:45.410 --> 34:47.048
THAT BURNED MY FACE.

34:47.080 --> 34:48.945
[ SQUEALING ]
AAH!

34:48.980 --> 34:50.447
AH!

34:50.480 --> 34:52.880
I'LL TAKE YOU DOWN
A ROCKY ROAD!
[ LAUGHS ]

34:52.920 --> 34:55.582
IT BURNS!
IN YOUR FACE!
AAH!

34:55.620 --> 34:57.884
Announcer: IT'S A LOW-DRIVING
KICK THAT LANDS AT THE 40.

34:57.920 --> 35:00.423
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

35:03.260 --> 35:04.966
Man:
FROM THE TOP OF THE VOLCANO,

35:05.000 --> 35:07.969
IN A FIERY BURST
OF SMOKE AND ASH,

35:08.000 --> 35:10.389
BUT THESE EXPLOSIONS
IN WHICH THE MAGMA IS...

35:10.440 --> 35:13.807
I'M SO STONED.
[ SIGHS ]

35:13.840 --> 35:15.808
...ARE ONLY THE MOST...

35:15.840 --> 35:18.400
I NEED A BATHROOM.

35:18.450 --> 35:20.975
DON'T MOVE.
I REMEMBER WHERE IT IS.

35:21.010 --> 35:24.138
...IS ONE IN WHICH LAVA POURS
FROM INSIDE THE VOLCANO

35:24.190 --> 35:25.987
OUT ONTO THE GROUND,

35:26.020 --> 35:31.481
FORMING A FAMILIAR MOLTEN RIVER
KNOWN AS A LAVA FLOW.

35:31.530 --> 35:34.124
GRADUALLY, THAT LAVA...

36:05.990 --> 36:07.321
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:10.700 --> 36:12.497
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:23.840 --> 36:25.671
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

37:12.730 --> 37:16.427
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

37:16.460 --> 37:20.863
...THE MOST POWERFUL
NUCLEAR DETONATION IN HISTORY.

37:20.900 --> 37:24.199
MORE THAN 36,000 PEOPLE DIED
AS THE RESULT OF THE ERUPTION.

37:24.240 --> 37:25.935
[ TV TURNS OFF ]

38:08.680 --> 38:11.148
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]
[ GASPS ]

38:11.180 --> 38:12.818
[ GASPS ]

38:12.850 --> 38:14.454
CALL ME.

38:37.310 --> 38:40.199
[ DOOR OPENS ]

38:50.220 --> 38:52.029
HOW'D IT GO?

38:55.330 --> 38:59.994
HE HAS A BRIEFCASE THAT HE TAKES
TO THE OFFICE EVERY DAY.

39:01.000 --> 39:02.695
GOOD.

39:02.740 --> 39:06.506
SO NEXT TIME YOU'RE THERE,
YOU'LL PUT THE BUG IN?

39:06.540 --> 39:09.031
YEP.

39:11.510 --> 39:13.398
[ SIGHS ]

39:15.180 --> 39:16.818
ANYTHING ELSE?

39:16.850 --> 39:20.183
HER PARENTS CAME HOME.

39:21.350 --> 39:24.217
SO I HAD TO RUN...

39:24.260 --> 39:27.149
LIKE A TEENAGER.

39:27.190 --> 39:31.524
THE WHOLE THING
WAS JUST...

39:31.570 --> 39:33.219
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:33.270 --> 39:35.329
OH, GOD.
I DON'T KNOW.

39:35.370 --> 39:37.395
ARE YOU STONED?

39:37.440 --> 39:39.931
[ SIGHS ] I'M OKAY.

39:47.380 --> 39:49.610
[ SIGHS ]

39:54.790 --> 39:59.079
DO YOU THINK ABOUT
WHEN WE LEARNED TO DO THIS?

40:00.960 --> 40:02.894
NO.

40:14.740 --> 40:16.571
[ WOMAN SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

40:31.760 --> 40:35.753
IT MUST BE DIFFERENT
FOR A MAN.

40:41.130 --> 40:43.439
I DON'T KNOW.

40:50.840 --> 40:55.140
YOU HAD TO FIND IT
IN YOUR MIND SOMEWHERE.

40:55.180 --> 40:57.774
[ BED RATTLING ]

40:57.820 --> 41:01.608
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

41:15.340 --> 41:20.664
THEY KEPT TELLING US WE HAD
TO MAKE IT REAL TO OURSELVES.

41:33.320 --> 41:35.811
[ SIGHS ]

41:35.860 --> 41:37.851
[ SIGHS ]

41:41.230 --> 41:43.790
IS THAT WHAT YOU DO
WITH MARTHA?

41:43.830 --> 41:47.129
I GUESS.

41:47.170 --> 41:48.990
[ SIGHS ]

41:49.040 --> 41:51.338
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT KIMBERLY?

41:51.370 --> 41:53.838
[ SIGHS ]

42:00.580 --> 42:03.014
I FEEL BAD
FOR KIMBERLY.

42:05.350 --> 42:09.810
I HAVEN'T SLEPT
WITH HER, NO.

42:09.860 --> 42:11.555
SHOULD I SLEEP
WITH HER?

42:11.590 --> 42:14.718
I DON'T KNOW.

42:14.760 --> 42:17.649
NO, HONESTLY.
I'M ASKING YOU.

42:17.700 --> 42:21.227
HONESTLY, I DON'T KNOW.

42:21.270 --> 42:23.761
[ SIGHS ]

42:37.080 --> 42:40.049
DO YOU HAVE TO MAKE IT REAL
WITH ME?

42:43.460 --> 42:45.553
SOMETIMES.

42:51.560 --> 42:53.391
NOT NOW.
